
🔍 **DMS Pre-Migration Database Assessment Tool**

A comprehensive database discovery and assessment tool for planning AWS DMS PostgreSQL migrations. Run this **before** starting any migration to understand the source database complexity and get tailored recommendations.

---

📋 **Overview**

This tool connects to a source PostgreSQL database and generates a detailed report covering 16 assessment areas. It produces a **migration complexity score** (LOW/MEDIUM/HIGH) with specific recommendations for your migration approach.

---

⚙️ **Prerequisites**

- 🖥️ **bash 4.0+**
- 🐘 **psql** client installed

  ```bash
  # macOS
  brew install libpq

  # Ubuntu/Debian
  sudo apt-get install postgresql-client

  # Amazon Linux
  sudo yum install postgresql
  ```

- 📦 **jq** (optional, for JSON parsing)
- 🌐 Network access to the source PostgreSQL database

---

🚀 **Usage**

```bash
chmod +x db-assessment.sh
./db-assessment.sh
```

You will be prompted for:

| Prompt | Default | Description |
|---|---|---|
| 🖥️ DB Host | — | Source database hostname or IP |
| 🔌 DB Port | `5432` | PostgreSQL port |
| 🗄️ DB Name | `postgres` | Database name |
| 👤 DB Username | `postgres` | Database user (needs read access to system catalogs) |
| 🔑 DB Password | — | Database password |

---

🔎 **Assessment Areas**

| | Area | What It Checks | Migration Impact |
|---|---|---|---|
| 1️⃣ | **Database Overview** | Total size, PostgreSQL version | Migration type decision, version compatibility |
| 2️⃣ | **Schema Summary** | Schema count, sizes | Multi-schema DMS table mappings |
| 3️⃣ | **Table Inventory** | Top 30 tables by size, row counts, index sizes | Full load parallelism, largest table planning |
| 4️⃣ | **Data Type Distribution** | Column types across all tables | Type compatibility, DMS type mappings |
| 5️⃣ | **LOB/Large Columns** | BYTEA, TEXT, JSON, JSONB, XML, arrays | DMS LOB mode settings (FullLobMode vs LimitedLobMode) |
| 6️⃣ | **Index Summary** | Index types (BTREE, GIN, GiST, BRIN, HASH, UNIQUE) | Create indexes post-load for faster migration |
| 7️⃣ | **Foreign Keys** | FK constraints between tables | Disable during load, re-enable after |
| 8️⃣ | **Triggers** | Table triggers | Disable on target during migration |
| 9️⃣ | **Views** | View definitions | Migrate via `pg_dump --schema-only` |
| 🔟 | **Functions/Procedures** | Stored procedures, functions, aggregates | Migrate via `pg_dump --schema-only` |
| 1️⃣1️⃣ | **Extensions** | Installed PostgreSQL extensions | Must be installed on target before migration |
| 1️⃣2️⃣ | **Sequences** | Sequence names and current values | Sync after CDC cutover |
| 1️⃣3️⃣ | **Partitioned Tables** | Partition strategy (RANGE/LIST/HASH), partition count | DMS needs special table mapping rules |
| 1️⃣4️⃣ | **Database Roles** | Users, permissions, superuser flags | Recreate on target account |
| 1️⃣5️⃣ | **Replication Status** | WAL level, existing replication slots | CDC readiness |
| 1️⃣6️⃣ | **Complexity Score** | Weighted score (0-20) | Migration approach recommendation |

---

📊 **Complexity Scoring**

The tool calculates a weighted complexity score based on findings:

| Factor | Weight | Condition |
|---|---|---|
| 💾 Database size | 1-3 | <100GB = 1, 100GB-1TB = 2, >1TB = 3 |
| 📄 LOB columns | 0-3 | None = 0, 1-20 = 1, >20 = 3 |
| 🔗 Foreign keys | 0-2 | None = 0, 1-50 = 1, >50 = 2 |
| ⚡ Triggers | 0-2 | None = 0, any = 2 |
| 🧩 Functions | 0-1 | None = 0, any = 1 |
| 👁️ Views | 0-1 | None = 0, any = 1 |
| 📦 Partitioned tables | 0-2 | None = 0, any = 2 |
| 📇 Indexes | 0-2 | <100 = 0, >100 = 2 |
| 🔢 Sequences | 0-1 | None = 0, any = 1 |

**Score Interpretation**

| Score | Complexity | Recommended Approach |
|---|---|---|
| **0-5** | 🟢 LOW | Standard DMS migration — run `dms-pg-migrate.sh` directly |
| **6-10** | 🟡 MEDIUM | DMS + schema migration — `pg_dump --schema-only` first, then DMS, then post-migration scripts |
| **11-20** | 🔴 HIGH | Full assessment needed — custom DMS table mappings, phased migration |

---

📄 **Output**

The tool outputs to both **terminal** and a **report file**:

```
📁 db-assessment-20260329-143021.txt
```

**Sample Output**

```
═══════════════════════════════════════════════════
  DATABASE ASSESSMENT REPORT
  Host: mydb.cluster-abc123.us-east-2.rds.amazonaws.com:5432/insurance_db
  Date: Sun Mar 29 14:30:21 CDT 2026
═══════════════════════════════════════════════════

1. DATABASE OVERVIEW
─────────────────────────────────────────────────
  database    | total_size | version
  insurance_db| 2.5 TB     | PostgreSQL 14.10

...

16. MIGRATION COMPLEXITY ASSESSMENT
═══════════════════════════════════════════════════

  Complexity: MEDIUM (8/20) — DMS + schema migration needed
  Recommended: pg_dump schema + dms-pg-migrate.sh + post-migration scripts

Migration Notes:
  ⚠ Large DB (2500GB) — use full-load then CDC (two-phase)
  ⚠ Some LOB columns (12) — check LobMaxSize setting
  ⚠ Has FKs (45) — DMS does not migrate FKs, add post-migration
  ⚠ Has triggers (8) — disable on target during load
  ⚠ Has functions (23) — migrate via pg_dump --schema-only
  ⚠ Has views (15) — migrate via pg_dump --schema-only
  ⚠ Has sequences (30) — sync after CDC cutover

═══════════════════════════════════════════════════
  Summary: 245 tables | 2500GB | 312 indexes
  45 FKs | 8 triggers | 23 functions
  15 views | 30 sequences | 0 partitions
═══════════════════════════════════════════════════
```

---

🔐 **Required Database Permissions**

The assessment user needs **read-only** access to system catalogs:

```sql
-- ✅ Minimum permissions
GRANT CONNECT ON DATABASE mydb TO assessment_user;
GRANT USAGE ON SCHEMA public TO assessment_user;
GRANT SELECT ON ALL TABLES IN SCHEMA public TO assessment_user;

-- 🌟 For full assessment (recommended)
GRANT pg_read_all_stats TO assessment_user;
```

---

🧰 **Migration Toolkit**

This tool is part of the DMS PostgreSQL Migration Toolkit:

| Script | Purpose | When to Run |
|---|---|---|
| 🔍 **`db-assessment.sh`** | Database discovery & complexity scoring | ⬅️ **Run first** |
| 🚀 `dms-pg-migrate.sh` | Full migration (VPC peering → RDS → DMS → full load → CDC) | Migration execution |
| ✂️ `dms-cutover.sh` | Stop CDC, verify data, update Secrets Manager | Cutover day |
| 🧹 `dms-cleanup.sh` | Remove all DMS resources, peering, routes | After migration confirmed stable |

---

🗺️ **Workflow**

```
  🔍 Run db-assessment.sh on source DB
              │
              ▼
  📊 Review complexity score & notes
              │
              ├── 🟢 LOW (0-5)  ──────► 🚀 Run dms-pg-migrate.sh directly
              │
              ├── 🟡 MEDIUM (6-10) ──► 📦 pg_dump --schema-only first
              │                        🚀 then dms-pg-migrate.sh
              │                        🔧 then post-migration scripts (FKs, triggers, views)
              │
              └── 🔴 HIGH (11-20) ──► 📋 Detailed planning required
                                      🗂️ Custom DMS table mappings
                                      📐 Phased migration approach
              │
              ▼
  ✂️ Run dms-cutover.sh on cutover day
              │
              ▼
  🧹 Run dms-cleanup.sh after confirmed stable
```

---

⚠️ **Limitations**

- 🌐 Requires direct network access to the source database
- 📊 Some checks require `pg_read_all_stats` role for accurate row counts
- 📦 Partitioned table detection requires PostgreSQL 10+
- 🧩 `prokind` column (function type) requires PostgreSQL 11+
- 🔌 Does not assess application-level dependencies (connection strings, ORMs, etc.)

